    {
      "id": "ce19e04f-1018-4cbb-9760-10ff33826c45",
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "Exercise 2: Write a function is_BST to check if the input root node is the root of a BST\n\n\nTest cases:\n    BinaryTreeNode<Integer> n2 = new BinaryTreeNode<Integer>(2, null, new       BinaryTreeNode<Integer>(-2, null, null));\n    BinaryTreeNode<Integer> n4 = new BinaryTreeNode<Integer>(4, new BinaryTreeNode<Integer>(3, null, null), new BinaryTreeNode<Integer>(7, null, null));\n    BinaryTreeNode<Integer> root = new BinaryTreeNode<Integer>(5, n2, n9);\n",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "markdown",
        "id": "ce19e04f-1018-4cbb-9760-10ff33826c45"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "303b613a-7369-40dc-89f2-20203875b1cc",
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": " public boolean is_BST(BinaryTreeNode<Integer> root){\r\n    return is_BST_(root, null, null);\r\n }\r\n public boolean is_BST_(BinaryTreeNode<Integer> node, Integer min, Integer max){\r\n    if(node == null){\r\n        return true;\r\n    }\r\n    else{\r\n        if(min != null && node.data.compareTo(min)<0 ){\r\n            return false;\r\n        }\r\n        if(max!= null && node.data.compareTo(max)>0){\r\n            return false;\r\n        }\r\n        return (is_BST_(node.left, min, node.data) && is_BST_(node.right, node.data, max));\r\n    }\r\n }\r\n BinaryTreeNode<Integer> n2 = new BinaryTreeNode<Integer>(2, null, new BinaryTreeNode<Integer>(1, null, null));\r\n    BinaryTreeNode<Integer> n4 = new BinaryTreeNode<Integer>(4, new BinaryTreeNode<Integer>(3, null, null), new BinaryTreeNode<Integer>(7, null, null));\r\n    BinaryTreeNode<Integer> root = new BinaryTreeNode<Integer>(5, n2, n4);\r\n\r\nIO.println(is_BST(root));",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "java",
